Fix two defaults for the cross-compile case: (1) sizeof(long) = 8 and
(2) the cross-compiler produces ELF type.  These involve runtime
tests, so libelf just guesses the answer in the cross-compile case.

Note: technically, we're not guaranteed that these defaults are always
correct, eg sizeof(long) = 8.  So, we could use separate conditional
patches for BG/P, BG/Q, MIC, etc.


diff -Naurb libelf-0.8.13.orig/configure libelf-0.8.13/configure
--- libelf-0.8.13.orig/configure	2008-05-23 03:18:03.000000000 -0500
+++ libelf-0.8.13/configure	2013-04-25 18:32:07.438202712 -0500
@@ -1556,7 +1556,7 @@
   echo $ac_n "(cached) $ac_c" 1>&6
 else
   if test "$cross_compiling" = yes; then
-  ac_cv_sizeof_long=4
+  ac_cv_sizeof_long=8
 else
   cat > conftest.$ac_ext <<EOF
 #line 1563 "configure"
